# Pin Map

## Motor Driver (L298N)
- ENA (PWM) → PA8 (TIM1_CH1)
- ENB (PWM) → PA9 (TIM1_CH2)
- IN1 → PB0
- IN2 → PB1
- IN3 → PB2
- IN4 → PB10

## Bluetooth (HC-05)
- HC-05 TX → STM32 RX (USART2_RX)
- HC-05 RX ← STM32 TX (USART2_TX) (use voltage divider)
- VCC → 5V
- GND → GND

# Bluetooth App + Commands

## App Used
- (put the app name here, e.g., “Serial Bluetooth Terminal” on Android)

## HC-05 Settings
- Baud rate: 9600
- Pairing PIN: 1234 or 0000

## Commands
- `F` = Forward
- `B` = Backward
- `S` = Stop
- `L` = Left
- `R` = Right

# Bill of Materials (BOM)

- STM32F407 board
- L298N driver module
- 2x DC motors
- HC-05 Bluetooth module
- Battery pack (4xAA or equivalent)
- Jumper wires
- Breadboard 
- Resistors for voltage divider (1k + 2k)

